 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# 🕌 OpenBayan: Semantic Vector Search Research (Optimized)\n",
    "\n",
    "This notebook explores the implementation of **Semantic Vector Search** using:\n",
    "1. **Ollama**: For generating 1024-dimensional embeddings using `mxbai-embed-large`.\n",
    "2. **SurrealDB 3.0**: For storing documents and performing high-performance vector similarity search.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Optimization Strategy:\n",
    "- **Display**: Uthmani text (with Harakat).\n",
    "- **Embedding**: Simple-Clean text (Normalized).\n",
    "- **LLM Context**: Simple-Clean text.\n",
    "\n",
    "This strategy ensures the highest semantic accuracy while maintaining beautiful Arabic typography in the UI."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import os\n",
    "import requests\n",
    "import re\n",
    "from surrealdb import Surreal\n",
    "\n",
    "# Configuration\n",
    "SURREAL_URL = \"ws://surrealdb:8000/rpc\"\n",
    "OLLAMA_URL = \"http://100.121.116.17:11434\"  # External Ollama Host\n",
    "EMBED_MODEL = \"mxbai-embed-large:latest\"\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"Setup complete.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Multi-Format Fetching & Chunking\n",
    "We fetch both formats and split them simultaneously to keep segments aligned."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def chunk_text(text):\n",
    "    # Quranic stop marks for alignment\n",
    "    waqf_marks = r'[\\u06d6-\\u06db]'\n",
    "    chunks = re.split(waqf_marks, text)\n",
    "    return [c.strip() for c in chunks if c.strip()]\n",
    "\n",
    "# Fetch Ayat al-Kursi (2:255)\n",
    "res_u = requests.get(\"https://api.alquran.cloud/v1/ayah/2:255/quran-uthmani\").json()[\"data\"]\n",
    "res_c = requests.get(\"https://api.alquran.cloud/v1/ayah/2:255/quran-simple-clean\").json()[\"data\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "text_uthmani = res_u[\"text\"]\n",
    "text_clean = res_c[\"text\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "chunks_u = chunk_text(text_uthmani)\n",
    "chunks_c = chunk_text(text_clean)\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"Total Semantic Chunks: {len(chunks_u)}\")\n",
    "if len(chunks_u) == len(chunks_c):\n",
    "    print(\"✅ Alignment Verified\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Optimized Ingestion\n",
    "We generate vectors from the **Clean** text but store the **Uthmani** text for display."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_embedding(text):\n",
    "    response = requests.post(\n",
    "        f\"{OLLAMA_URL}/api/embeddings\",\n",
    "        json={\n",
    "            \"model\": EMBED_MODEL,\n",
    "            \"prompt\": text\n",
    "        }\n",
    "    )\n",
    "    return response.json()[\"embedding\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "with Surreal(SURREAL_URL) as db:\n",
    "    db.signin({\"user\": \"root\", \"pass\": \"root\"})\n",
    "    db.use(\"main\", \"main\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Clear existing sentences\n",
    "    db.query(\"DELETE sentence\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    for i in range(len(chunks_u)):\n",
    "        # EMBED THE CLEAN VERSION\n",
    "        embedding = get_embedding(chunks_c[i])\n",
    "        \n",
    "        db.query(\n",
    "            \"CREATE sentence CONTENT $record\",\n",
    "            {\n",
    "                \"record\": {\n",
    "                    \"text\": chunks_u[i],             # Display (Uthmani)\n",
    "                    \"simple_clean_text\": chunks_c[i],# Search Reference (Clean)\n",
    "                    \"chunk_index\": i,\n",
    "                    \"source_type\": \"quran\",\n",
    "                    \"embedding\": embedding,          # Derived from Clean\n",
    "                    \"llm_context\": text_clean        # Use Clean context for LLM\n",
    "                }\n",
    "            }\n",
    "        )\n",
    "print(\"✅ Optimized Ingestion complete.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. High-Confidence Semantic Search\n",
    "Searching against vectors derived from clean text yields significantly higher similarity scores."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def search(query_text, limit=3):\n",
    "    embedding = get_embedding(query_text)\n",
    "    with Surreal(SURREAL_URL) as db:\n",
    "        db.signin({\"user\": \"root\", \"pass\": \"root\"})\n",
    "        db.use(\"main\", \"main\")\n",
    "        \n",
    "        # Note: we are searching using the 'embedding' field which we just \n",
    "        # populated with vectors generated from clean text.\n",
    "        results = db.query(\n",
    "            \"\"\"\n",
    "            SELECT \n",
    "                text, \n",
    "                vector::similarity::cosine(embedding, $embedding) AS sim\n",
    "            FROM sentence \n",
    "            ORDER BY sim DESC\n",
    "            LIMIT $limit;\n",
    "            \"\"\",\n",
    "            {\"embedding\": embedding, \"limit\": limit}\n",
    "        )\n",
    "        return results\n",
    "\n",
    "# Try a conceptual query\n",
    "query = \"The Ever-Living Protector\"\n",
    "print(f\"Searching for conceptual match for: '{query}'\\n\")\n",
    "\n",
    "search_results = search(query)\n",
    "for i, r in enumerate(search_results):\n",
    "    print(f\"{i+1}. [Similarity: {r['sim']:.4f}] {r['text']}\")"
   ]
  }\n",
 ],\n",
